Chilean Stocks: Corpbanca Falls; Lan Airlines, Salfacorp Rise

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-09-01T20:02:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/chile-stocks-bci-corpbanca-decline-salfacorp-advances.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:15 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index rose 0.5 percent to 4,308.13.  Corpbanca (CORPBANC)  ,  Chile ’s sixth-largest lender by
assets, fell 1.8 percent to 6.936 pesos, the steepest drop in
two weeks. Chilean banks posted a 17 percent drop in profits in
July from June, according to a statement posted on the banking
regulator’s website yesterday.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)  ,  Latin America ’s largest airline
by market value, rose 2.1 percent to 13,240 pesos, its highest
price in six weeks. Chile’s constitutional court rejected a
request from local rival Pal Airlines to block Lan’s planned
takeover of  Brazil ’s Tam SA.  Salfacorp SA (SALFACOR)   rose 3.2 percent to 1,520 pesos,
its biggest gain in three weeks. Chile’s largest construction
company reported a 38 percent increase in second-quarter profit
to 3.66 billion pesos ($8 million) from 2.66 billion pesos a
year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
